CodeList.Name: PK Parameters

Description.TranslatedText: Parameters used to describe the time-concentration curve.

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accum Ratio AUC T1 to T2 norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accum Ratio AUC T1 to T2 norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The area under the curve from T1 to T2 at steady state divided by the area under the curve from T1 to T2 during the initial dosing interval, each divided by the associated dose.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Accumulation Ratio AUC T1 to T2 Normalized by Dose

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accum Ratio AUC to Last Nonzero Conc
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accum Ratio AUC to Last Nonzero Conc
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the last measurable concentration divided by the area under the curve from the time of dosing to the last measurable concentration during the initial dosing interval.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Accumulation Ratio AUC to Last Nonzero Concentration

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accum Ratio AUCTAU norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accum Ratio AUCTAU norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The area under the curve (AUCTAU) at steady state divided by the area under the curve (AUCTAU) over the initial dosing interval, each divided by the associated dose.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Accumulation Ratio AUC Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Dose

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accum Ratio Cmax norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accum Ratio Cmax norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The maximum concentration at steady state divided by the maximum concentration during the initial dosing interval, each divided by the associated dose.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Accumulation Ratio Cmax Normalized by Dose

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accum Ratio Cmin norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accum Ratio Cmin norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The minimum concentration at steady state divided by the minimum concentration during the initial dosing interval, each divided by the associated dose.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Accumulation Ratio Cmin Normalized by Dose

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accum Ratio Ctrough norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accum Ratio Ctrough norm by dose
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The trough concentration at steady state divided by the trough concentration during the initial dosing interval, each divided by the associated dose.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Accumulation Ratio Ctrough Normalized by Dose

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accumulation Index using Lambda z
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accumulation Index using Lambda z
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: Predicted accumulation ratio for area under the curve (AUC) calculated using the Lambda z estimated from single dose data.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Accumulation Index using Lambda z

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accumulation Ratio AUC from T1 to T2
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accumulation Ratio AUC from T1 to T2

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accumulation Ratio AUCTAU
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Accumulation Ratio AUCTAU

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: Accumulation Ratio Cmax

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Amt Rec from T1 to T2
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC over the interval from T1 to T2.
